@Dhruv Rathee Hill Valley divide: The MLAs of the hills do not care about their hills, contrarily they build their houses and reside in Imphal valley. So, the sad part is that they donтАЩt do any development work for their respective hill constituencies because they are not staying there itself.
Inner line permit: The tribals are already protected by scheduled tribes category and do not need ILP. The meiteis in the Imphal valley area are not scheduled tribes so, they need ILP. If they become scheduled tribes, they will not need ILP. Moreover, tribes from the hills have freedom to buy land and reside in valley but meiteis cannot buy land and reside in the hills.
Kuki people: They do not belong to Manipur before 1800. They were given shelter with the recommendation from the Britishers. Nagas who were living with the meiteis for very long time since time immemorial used to get more seats in Manipur Legislative Assembly than Kukis, now both nagas and Kukis  they have equal seats now. The original inhabitants, specifically in the hill districts will get lesser seats in the future. The Kukis favoured illegal migrants from their people from Myanmar and Bangladesh.
